# Platform Testing and Release Rules

## Intent
Define minimum quality and safety gates before code reaches users.

## Mandatory (MVP Phase Exemption)
**NOTE: For MVP phase only (temporary), automated testing requirements are deferred per product decision. Testing will be restored for post-MVP hardening phases. See Rule 119 for CI gate changes.**

- ~~Every feature must include automated tests at the right layer (unit/integration/e2e as applicable).~~ [DEFERRED FOR MVP]
- ~~Plugin commands and permission checks must have positive and negative tests.~~ [DEFERRED FOR MVP]
- ~~Critical plugin messaging workflows (including Chyme chat) must have regression coverage on web and mobile clients.~~ [DEFERRED FOR MVP]
- ~~Security/privacy gates must run in GitHub Actions and block promotion on failure.~~ [DEFERRED FOR MVP]
- Rollout plans must include monitoring, rollback criteria, and owner assignment.

## Release Readiness
- Confirm contract compatibility for web/mobile/backend versions.
- Confirm observability dashboards and alerting exist for new critical paths.
- Confirm changelog/operational notes for support and incident responders.

## Prohibited
- Shipping untested critical-path changes.
- Enabling production-only behavior without feature flag or rollback strategy.
- Deploying to production outside approved GitHub Actions workflows.